Woof.;    In this house, man and dogs speak as one. Their relationship isunusually tender. One need only listen while Wegman murmurs to Fay Ray and

Battina, her 1 1/2-year-old daughter.; On Valentine's Day, for example, he said, "I'll take them out and play with them longer."
"When Bill leaves, Batty howls," said Andrea Beeman, an assistant to Wegman.; Man and dog; Their home is one floor of a former Orthodox synagogue on the Lower East Side of Manhattan.
; A dog's life; Had he been a different breed he would have been a "character actor," Wegman said, "like Lassie."
